dataLineage.statement: 2014-01-10 - Errors in data resolved. Mayotte now an overseas department of France and therefore merged with the France polygon. Saint Barth√©lemy now an overseas collectivity of France and is removed from the France record and a new record with the ISO code BL is created.

prcStep.description:
In 2008 the attributes NAME_GAUL, ISO3_CODE, SVRG_UN and CAPT were added to the original table and filled with information from the GAUL_2006 country dataset.
Some new CNTR_CODEs were added or filled for: RS (Serbia); XC --> XO (disputed areas). In 2009 the attributes CENT_MERI and LAT_ORIG were added for cartographic purposes (the Urban Audit Mapping tool uses these attributes).
2010: Some new CNTR_CODEs were added: EL for GR

dataSource.srcDesc: The source of this table was the former ADCNPS.INF table in the coverage version of the GISCO reference database. Later GAUL 2006 attribute information was added GAUKL 2008 attribute information was added

DQDomConsis.measDesc: The integrity and cardinality of the relationships (conceptual and implemented) was checked by enforcing primary and foreign key integrity constraints in Oracle. The constraints referencing coded value domain tables were a test of domain consistency.
DQDomConsis.evalMethDesc: Errors will show during creation of integrity constraints in Oracle. Constraints will not be applicable in case of violations to the consistency.

ConResult.conExpl: No errors occurred, so the integrity of all primary and foreign keys was confirmed. All the values of each coded value attribute are compliant to the domains (except for any NULL values). The cardinality can only be confirmed where it is strict enough for this test to detect errors.

DQConcConsis.measDesc: All feature classes, attribute tables and relationship classes should be present

ConResult.conExpl: All feature classes, attribute tables and relationship classes are present
